    <h3>EHDSAlert → Flag</h3>
    <p class="lead">
      This page describes the element-by-element mapping from the <strong>EHDSAlert</strong> logical model to the FHIR <code>Flag</code> (or equivalent alert/clinical warning profile) used in this Implementation Guide. Alerts convey critical safety or clinical information that should be surfaced whenever the patient record is accessed.
    </p>
    <div class="legend">
      <strong>Relationship legend</strong>
      <dl>
        <dt>equal</dt><dd>Semantically equivalent.</dd>
        <dt>narrower</dt><dd>FHIR is more specific / more constrained.</dd>
        <dt>relatedto</dt><dd>Conceptually aligned but requires interpretation or depends on context.</dd>
        <dt>unmatched</dt><dd>No direct equivalent in this FHIR profile/datatype.</dd>
      </dl>
    </div>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table summary="EHDSAlert → Flag">
        <caption>EHDSAlert → Flag</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th colspan="2" class="src-head">EHDSAlert (Logical Model)</th>
            <th class="relhead">Relationship</th>
            <th colspan="3" class="tgt-head">Flag (Alert)</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th class="src-sub">Element</th>
            <th class="src-sub">Description</th>
            <th class="relsub">Relation</th>
            <th class="tgt-sub">Element</th>
            <th class="tgt-sub">Description</th>
            <th class="tgt-sub">Notes</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>identifier</td>
            <td>Identifier for the alert entry.</td>
            <td>equal</td>
            <td>identifier</td>
            <td>Business identifier for the flag.</td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>status</td>
            <td>Lifecycle status of the alert (active, entered-in-error, etc.).</td>
            <td>equal</td>
            <td>status</td>
            <td>Indicates if the flag is active, inactive, etc.</td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>category</td>
            <td>High-level classification of the alert (clinical safety, admin).</td>
            <td>equal</td>
            <td>category</td>
            <td>Clinical / administrative category.</td>
            <td>CodeableConcept.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>code</td>
            <td>Specific coded meaning of the alert.</td>
            <td>equal</td>
            <td>code</td>
            <td>Issue being highlighted.</td>
            <td>Often includes human-readable display.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>subject</td>
            <td>Subject (typically the patient) this alert refers to.</td>
            <td>equal</td>
            <td>subject</td>
            <td>Who/what the flag is about.</td>
            <td>Reference to Patient / Animal Patient.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>period</td>
            <td>Period of alert relevance.</td>
            <td>equal</td>
            <td>period</td>
            <td>Time period when the flag is active.</td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>author</td>
            <td>Who created/issued the alert.</td>
            <td>equal</td>
            <td>author</td>
            <td>Creator of the flag.</td>
            <td>Could reference PractitionerRole, Practitioner, or Organization.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
